Mr. UDALL. I see my time has expired. If the Chairwoman would

indulge me for 30 more seconds?

Speaking to your comment about shading not only with leaves on
trees  but  the  tree  branches  themselves,  that  was  one  of  the  proc-
esses we had to go through. We had a big old cottonwood tree that
was  blocking  at  certain  times  of  the  day  the  system,  and  I  found
out  in  the  process  of  installing  the  system  that  if  you  have  any
shading  on  any  part  of  the  system,  it  affects  the  overall  system  in
very dramatic ways. So we had to make the decision. It was almost
like  letting  go  of  your  firstborn  child,  taking  down  this  tree,  but  I
was  convinced  that  taking  down  the  tree  was  worth  the  pain  be-

